riefs UN General Assembly on R2P, 9 August 2010]\n* [http://mantlethought.org/roundtable/r2p Whose Responsibility to Protect?], debate between four R2P practitioners, October 2009.\n* [[Newt Gingrich]] and [[George J. Mitchell]], [http://www.aei.org/publications/filter.all,pubID.23488/pub_detail.asp Report Card from America: UN Reform], [[International Herald Tribune]], 28 November 2005 ([[American Enterprise Institute]])\n* [http://globalr2p.org/ Global Centre for the Responsibility to Protect]\n* [http://www.responsibilitytoprotect.org/ International Coalition for the Responsibility to Protect]\n* [http://www.r2pasiapacific.org/ Asia-Pacific Centre for R2P]\n\n[[Category:International relations theory]]\n[[Category:Responsibility to protect]]\n[[Category:2005 in international relations]]\n[[Category:Genocide prevention]]\n", "name_user": "JustinMal1", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eSyria:grammar", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Responsibility_to_protect"}
{"title_page": "Chandigarh Group of Colleges", "text_new": "<ref></ref>{{Use Indian English|date=July 2018}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2011}}\n{{Infobox university\n|established = 2001\n|name = Chandigarh Group of Colleges\n|image = CGC Main Gate.jpg\n|caption = Main gate of Chandigarh Group of Colleges\n|type = [[College]]\n|chairman = Satnam Singh Sandhu\n|president = Rashpal Singh Dhaliwal\n|director  = \n|city = Landran and Jhanjheri in [[Sahibzada Ajit Singh Nagar district|Mohali district]]\n|state = [[Punjab, India|Punjab]]\n|country = [[India]]\n|campus = [[urban area|Urban]]\n|affiliation = [[I. K. Gujral Punjab Technical University]]\n|website = {{URL|https://www.cgc.edu.in/}}\n}}\n\nThe '''Chandigarh Group of Colleges''' (or '''CGC''') are the [[educational institution]]s located in [[Sahibzada Ajit Singh Nagar district]] of [[Punjab, India|Punjab]] in short distance from cities of [[Chandigarh]] and [[Mohali]]. Chandigarh Group of Colleges was established in 2001 at Landran<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.aspiringminds.com/featured-campus/chandigarh-group-of-colleges-landran|title=Chandigarh Group of Colleges, Landran|website=www.aspiringminds.com|language=en|access-date=2018-07-26}}</ref> initially and at Jhanjheri in 2012.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cgc.ac.in/about-cgc-jhanjeri.html|title=CGC Jhanjeri|website=Chandigarh Group of Colleges}}</ref> In 2009, Chandigarh Group of Colleges Gharuan was established as Punjab's first integrated campus.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://indianexpress.com/article/cities/chandigarh/integrated-campus-to-be-set-up-in-mohali-village/|title=Integrated campus to be set up in Mohali village|date=2009-07-07|work=The Indian Express|access-date=2018-07-26|language=en-US}}</ref> All the colleges under the aegis of Chandigarh Group of Colleges are affiliated to I. K. Gujral Punjab Technical University (IKGPTU) Jalandhar and have been approved by '''All India Council for Technical Education (AICTE)''' or respective managing bodies by Govt. of India<ref>https://www.cgc.edu.in/approvals/</ref>. In 2012, CGC Gharuan campus was granted university status<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/chandigarh/punjab-cabinet-okays-chandigarh-varsity-in-pvt-sector/story-Y3LOKa81vwMupXbZTHy4uJ.html|title=Punjab cabinet okays Chandigarh varsity in pvt sector|date=2012-04-23|work=hindustan times|access-date=2018-07-26|language=en}}</ref> as [[Chandigarh University]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/chandigarh/candidates-for-cu-landing-at-pu/articleshow/64548421.cms|title=Candidates for Chandigarh University landing at Panjab University - Times of India|work=The Times of India|access-date=2018-07-26}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/punjab/mohali-marker-chandigarh-university-where-pupils-get-ready-for-jobs/story-rxDhKB6SuhJnohBXykpLYM.html|title=Mohali Marker: Chandigarh University, where pupils get ready for jobs|date=2017-09-09|work=hindustan times|access-date=2018-07-26|language=en}}</ref>\n\n==Research & Development==\nChandigarh Group of Colleges is among top 10 institutes of India in terms of number of patents filed.<ref>{{cite web | title=CGC Landran among top 10 institutions in filing patents | website=Tribuneindia News Service | date=2018-05-03 | url=https://www.tribuneindia.com/news/chandigarh/cgc-landran-among-top-10-institutions-in-filing-patents/583464.html | access-date=2018-07-26}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://punjabnewsexpress.com/campus-buzz/news/cgc-landran-in-countrys-top-ten-institutions-for-most-patents-filed-in-a-single-year-74888.aspx|title=CGC Landran in country\u2019s top ten institutions for most patents filed in a single year|website=punjabnewsexpress.com|access-date=2018-07-26}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | last=Roy | first=Vijay C | title=Punjab institutes wake up to patenting innovations | website=Tribune News Service | date=2018-06-03 | url=https://www.tribuneindia.com/news/kaleidoscope/punjab-institutes-wake-up-to-patenting-innovations/599197.html | access-date=2018-07-26}}</ref> CGC has [[Memorandum of understanding|MoU]] with [[National Institute of Electronics & Information Technology]] for Entrepreneurship, R&D Projects and training.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://nielit.gov.in/nielit-news-gallery?gallery=10512|title=MOU between NIELIT Chandigarh and CGC Landran|language=en|access-date=2018-07-26}}</ref> CGC is member of [[Artificial intelligence|AI]] and [[Deep learning]] project under Newton Bhabha Fund sanctioned by UK's [[Royal Academy of Engineering]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.5dariyanews.com/news/230281-CGC-Landran-becomes-zonal-partner-of-project-on-AI-and-Deep-Learning|title=CGC Landran becomes zonal partner of project on AI and Deep Learning|work=5 Dariya News|access-date=2018-07-26}}</ref> CGC was granted {{INRConvert|23|l}} aid by [[Indian Council of Medical Research]] for the development of nanotechnology-based lung cancer vaccine.<ref>{{cite web | title=CGC gets Rs 23 lakh grant to develop lung cancer vaccine | website=Tribuneindia News Service | date=2018-03-08 | url=https://www.tribuneindia.com/news/chandigarh/cgc-gets-rs-23-lakh-grant-to-develop-lung-cancer-vaccine/554604.html | access-date=2018-07-26}}</ref>\n\n==Campus Activities and Sports==\nCGC campus students get opportunities to be part of different cultural events like fashion shows<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://punjabnewsexpress.com/international/news/cgc-jhanjeri-organized-grand-fashion-show-59963.aspx|title=CGC Jhanjeri organized Grand Fashion Show|website=punjabnewsexpress.com|access-date=2018-07-26}}</ref>, Faculty felicitation<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://punjabnewsexpress.com/national/news/cgc-jhanjeri-honored-14-teachers-with-best-teachers-award-on-teachers-day-64765.aspx|title=CGC Jhanjeri honored 14 Teachers with Best Teachers Award on Teachers\u2019 Day|website=punjabnewsexpress.com|access-date=2018-07-26}}</ref>, [[NASA]] sponsored ''CanSat'' competition<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://punjabnewsex