Singh Dhaliwal\n|director  = \n|city = Landran and Jhanjheri in [[Sahibzada Ajit Singh Nagar district|Mohali district]]\n|state = [[Punjab, India|Punjab]]\n|country = [[India]]\n|campus = [[urban area|Urban]]\n|affiliation = [[I. K. Gujral Punjab Technical University]]\n|website = {{URL|https://www.cgc.edu.in/}}\n}}\n\nThe '''Chandigarh Group of Colleges''' (or '''CGC''') are the [[educational institution]]s located in [[Sahibzada Ajit Singh Nagar district]] of [[Punjab, India|Punjab]] in short distance from cities of [[Chandigarh]] and [[Mohali]]. Chandigarh Group of Colleges was established in 2001 at Landran<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.aspiringminds.com/featured-campus/chandigarh-group-of-colleges-landran|title=Chandigarh Group of Colleges, Landran|website=www.aspiringminds.com|language=en|access-date=2018-07-26}}</ref> initially and at Jhanjheri in 2012.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cgc.ac.in/about-cgc-jhanjeri.html|title=CGC Jhanjeri|website=Chandigarh Group of Colleges}}</ref> In 2009, Chandigarh Group of Colleges Gharuan was established as Punjab's first integrated campus.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://indianexpress.com/article/cities/chandigarh/integrated-campus-to-be-set-up-in-mohali-village/|title=Integrated campus to be set up in Mohali village|date=2009-07-07|work=The Indian Express|access-date=2018-07-26|language=en-US}}</ref> In 2012, CGC Gharuan campus was granted university status<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/chandigarh/punjab-cabinet-okays-chandigarh-varsity-in-pvt-sector/story-Y3LOKa81vwMupXbZTHy4uJ.html|title=Punjab cabinet okays Chandigarh varsity in pvt sector|date=2012-04-23|work=hindustan times|access-date=2018-07-26|language=en}}</ref> as [[Chandigarh University]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/chandigarh/candidates-for-cu-landing-at-pu/articleshow/64548421.cms|title=Candidates for Chandigarh University landing at Panjab University - Times of India|work=The Times of India|access-date=2018-07-26}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/punjab/mohali-marker-chandigarh-university-where-pupils-get-ready-for-jobs/story-rxDhKB6SuhJnohBXykpLYM.html|title=Mohali Marker: Chandigarh University, where pupils get ready for jobs|date=2017-09-09|work=hindustan times|access-date=2018-07-26|language=en}}</ref>\n\n==Research & Development==\nChandigarh Group of Colleges is among top 10 institutes of India in terms of number of patents filed.<ref>{{cite web | title=CGC Landran among top 10 institutions in filing patents | website=Tribuneindia News Service | date=2018-05-03 | url=https://www.tribuneindia.com/news/chandigarh/cgc-landran-among-top-10-institutions-in-filing-patents/583464.html | access-date=2018-07-26}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://punjabnewsexpress.com/campus-buzz/news/cgc-landran-in-countrys-top-ten-institutions-for-most-patents-filed-in-a-single-year-74888.aspx|title=CGC Landran in country\u2019s top ten institutions for most patents filed in a single year|website=punjabnewsexpress.com|access-date=2018-07-26}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | last=Roy | first=Vijay C | title=Punjab institutes wake up to patenting innovations | website=Tribune News Service | date=2018-06-03 | url=https://www.tribuneindia.com/news/kaleidoscope/punjab-institutes-wake-up-to-patenting-innovations/599197.html | access-date=2018-07-26}}</ref> CGC has [[Memorandum of understanding|MoU]] with [[National Institute of Electronics & Information Technology]] for Entrepreneurship, R&D Projects and training.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://nielit.gov.in/nielit-news-gallery?gallery=10512|title=MOU between NIELIT Chandigarh and CGC Landran|language=en|access-date=2018-07-26}}</ref> CGC is member of [[Artificial intelligence|AI]] and [[Deep learning]] project under Newton Bhabha Fund sanctioned by UK's [[Royal Academy of Engineering]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.5dariyanews.com/news/230281-CGC-Landran-becomes-zonal-partner-of-project-on-AI-and-Deep-Learning|title=CGC Landran becomes zonal partner of project on AI and Deep Learning|work=5 Dariya News|access-date=2018-07-26}}</ref> CGC was granted {{INRConvert|23|l}} aid by [[Indian Council of Medical Research]] for the development of nanotechnology-based lung cancer vaccine.<ref>{{cite web | title=CGC gets Rs 23 lakh grant to develop lung cancer vaccine | website=Tribuneindia News Service | date=2018-03-08 | url=https://www.tribuneindia.com/news/chandigarh/cgc-gets-rs-23-lakh-grant-to-develop-lung-cancer-vaccine/554604.html | access-date=2018-07-26}}</ref>\n\n==Campus Activities and Sports==\nCGC campus students get opportunities to be part of different cultural events like fashion shows<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://punjabnewsexpress.com/international/news/cgc-jhanjeri-organized-grand-fashion-show-59963.aspx|title=CGC Jhanjeri organized Grand Fashion Show|website=punjabnewsexpress.com|access-date=2018-07-26}}</ref>, Faculty felicitation<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://punjabnewsexpress.com/national/news/cgc-jhanjeri-honored-14-teachers-with-best-teachers-award-on-teachers-day-64765.aspx|title=CGC Jhanjeri honored 14 Teachers with Best Teachers Award on Teachers\u2019 Day|website=punjabnewsexpress.com|access-date=2018-07-26}}</ref>, [[NASA]] sponsored ''CanSat'' competition<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://punjabnewsexpress.com/campus-buzz/news/cgc-landran-teams-qualify-to-compete-in-the-final-round-of-cansat-2018-global-aerospace-competition-75463.aspx|title=CGC Landran teams qualify to compete in the final round of CanSat 2018 Global Aerospace Competition|website=punjabnewsexpress.com|access-date=2018-07-26}}</ref>, [[Ministry of Human Resource Development|MHRD]]'s Smart India Hackathon events<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://punjabnewsexpress.com/campus-buzz/news/smart-india-hackathon-2018-commences-at-cgc-landra-73877.aspx|title=Smart India Hackathon 2018 commences at CGC Landra|website=punjabnewsexpress.com|access-date=2018-07-26}}</ref>, Start up to Scale Up conferences<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.5dariyanews.com/news/227208-CGC-Jhanjeri-organized-4th-National-Conference-on-Start-Up-to-Scale-Up|title=CGC Jhanjeri organized 4th National Conference on  Start Up to Scale Up|work=5 Dariya News|access-date=2018-07-26}}</ref>, [[National Cadet Corps (India)|NCC]] best cadet<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://punjabnewsexpress.com/campus-buzz/news/cgc-students-bring-laurels-to-the-institution-72563.aspx|title=CGC students bring laurels to the institution|website=punjabnewsexpress.com|access-date=2018-07-26}}</ref>, Faculty Development Programmes<ref>{{cite web | title=Faculty development programme | website=Tribuneindia News Service | date=2018-01-06 | url=https://www.tribuneindia.com/news/chandigarh/faculty-development-programme/524229.html | access-date=2018-07-26}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.5dariyanews.com/news/234393-Annual-FDP-inaugurated-at-CGC-Landran|title=Annual FDP inaugurated at CGC Landran|work=5 Dariya News|access-date=2018-07-26}}</ref> apart from annual Techno cultural Fests.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/events/chandigarh/city-campuses-get-technically-competitive/articleshow/63529626.cms|title=City campuses get technically competitive - Times of India|work=The Times of India|access-date=2018-07-26}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | title=Cultural fest begins at CGC | website=Tribuneindia News Service | date=2018-02-03 | url=https://www.tribuneindia.com/news/chandigarh/cultural-fest-begins-at-cgc/538068.html | access-date=2018-07-26}}</ref> CGC students also participate in many sports tournaments and competitions in events such as Volleyball<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://punjabnewsexpress.com/campus-buzz/news/cgc-jhanjeri-girls-win-ptus-inter-college-volleyball-tournament--71635.aspx|title=CGC Jhanjeri Girls Win PTU\u2019s Inter College Volleyball Tournament|website=punjabnewsexpress.com|access-date=2018-07-26}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | title=CGC spikers clinch title | website=Tribuneindia News Service | date=2018-01-21 | url=htt